[09:43] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'would choose how long for the video to be. Now the resulting video is roughly 25 frames per second. So you need to basically divide the number of frames by 25 to calculate the duration of the'

[09:56] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'video. Now since our audio is 5 seconds, it\'s 5 * 25. So let\'s set the number of frames to 125. But note that you can also set this all the way up to 737'

[10:08] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'frames, which is roughly 29 seconds. For me, I\'m going to leave it at 125. And then for the number of inference steps, this is basically how many steps you want the AI to take before outputting'

[10:21] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your final video. In general, the more steps you have, the higher quality your video will be, but at a certain point, you\'re going to get diminishing returns. And then if you set this to a lower value, then it\'s going to generate'

[10:33] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'faster because it takes fewer steps, but you\'re going to sacrifice some quality. So, let\'s just leave this at the default of 10 steps. And then there\'s also this toggle for some advanced settings. Let\'s go over these really quickly. For'

[10:47] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'guidance, this is basically like how much you want the AI to follow your prompt. And then for the audio guidance, this is like how much you want the AI to lip-s sync to your audio. If you feel like the person isn\'t speaking the audio'

[10:59] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'accurately, you could set this to a higher value and see if that\'s any better. And then honestly, for the rest of these settings, I just leave it at the default. You can also activate tcash and meg cache here, which would speed up'

[11:11] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'your video generation even further. And it does this by basically skipping some of the steps that you specified up here. So, it\'s going to sacrifice some quality, but usually it\'s not really noticeable. And if you turn this setting'

